5-8th grade students, your family should have received a letter explaining SORA, our new digital library of eBooks and audio books. Check out what there is to read! Dog Man, the 2021 Nutmeg books, Harry Potter and Guts, just to name a few. To log in you need to download the SORA app on any device or use your browser and type in www.soraapp.com.

The first time you open the app or site, you will need to find our school district. We are Regional School District 1. After you select that, you will choose Salisbury Central from the dropdown menu, and log in with your schools Google username and password.

There are more directions on our school website on how to get started and a video explaining the app.

If you have any trouble logging in please let Mrs. Allyn know. Have fun reading this summer!

Dav Pilkey, the children’s author and illustrator behind award-winning and worldwide bestselling book series including Dog Man and Captain Underpants, is collaborating with the Library of Congress to serve children and families online during the coronavirus pandemic.

post_text: Salisbury Central, let’s make some hearts and show our unity! We can do this!
shared_text:
Region One School District
March 23 at 10:57 PM ·

We are announcing Region One Unity!

We are united in our quest to provide all of the support we can to our students, staff, and families in Region One.

We are asking staff, students, parents, and community members to place any kind of heart (paper, fabric, wood, etc.) on any place that can be seen by others-- your mailbox, inside of your car, your home-- so that everyone who sees a heart will know that our region is very strong. We are showing our strength in so many ways.

It's pretty simple. When you then leave your home for food or take a safe walk in the neighborhood, you can smile, when you see the hearts, knowing that we are all in this together.

#Region1Unity

AUDIBLE.COM
Stories Help. Audible Stories Lets Anyone, Anywhere, Listen for Free.

Read to a Child
March 20 at 2:57 PM ·

We applaud companies that serve the community. That's why we can't help but give a standing ovation to Audible who is opening up their entire Kids Lit library, which includes hundreds of titles for kids and families, for FREE "as long as schools are closed."

Parents and caretakers that are still looking for read aloud resources for kids who are home indefinitely from school can utilize Audibles Kids Library for absolutely free with unlimited listening opportunities in SIX different languages. Thank you Audible for participating in the movement to #HelpKidsRead

https://www.audible.com/about/newsroom/stories-help-audible-stories-lets-anyone-anywhere-listen-for-free/

post_text:
How would you like it if you went into the library to get your favorite book and found out you could no longer check it out because it is banned? That’s what happened to Amy Anne. This prompted her and her friends to take matters into their own hands. They started the B.B.L.L. (Banned Books Locker Library). They wanted the books available to all those that wanted to read them. You have to read this to find out what happens to the B.B.L.L.

This was another great book. I hope you will take some time this month to read it!

post_text: Ready for a good mystery thriller? Check out The Van Gogh Deception by Deron Hicks. No one knows his name. No one knows where he belongs. No one knows who he is. Not even him And what no one really knows is what might just get this mysterious boy killed. Arthur (as the tag on his jacket is labeled) can’t remember anything, but he knows things. Weird things. He knows what Paris is like. He knows what minerals are used in hundred year old paints. And he somehow knows everything about the long-lost Van Gogh collection that is opening at the National Gallery of Art. What he doesn’t know is why in the past 24 hours, everything has been turned upside down. A mysterious piece of plastic, kidnapping, and frantic escape are just parts of the startling revelation taking place. Filled with twists and turns, Art is not sure who he is and what he knows – but it’s enough to get him killed..

I hope you are enjoying your summer! Be sure to write your books down so we can do well on the summer reading challenge!

post_text:
Due to the bad weather forecasts through multiple sources the Regional Track Meet is cancelled for tomorrow Tuesday, May 28th. This was a group decision made by all the PE teachers. The safety of the students is our highest priority. We felt that running on a wet track/grass would be too dangerous and would result in a greater chance of injury. Currently there is no confirmed rain date for the Regional Track Meet but all the PE teachers and their principals are working hard to determine when and if that will be possible. We thank you for your understanding and patience.

Best,
Region One PE Teachers
text:
Due to the bad weather forecasts through multiple sources the Regional Track Meet is cancelled for tomorrow Tuesday, May 28th. This was a group decision made by all the PE teachers. The safety of the students is our highest priority. We felt that running on a wet track/grass would be too dangerous and would result in a greater chance of injury. Currently there is no confirmed rain date for the Regional Track Meet but all the PE teachers and their principals are working hard to determine when and if that will be possible. We thank you for your understanding and patience.

Best,
Region One PE Teachers

North Canaan Elementary School can be very proud of performances of Disney's "Mulan, Jr." on March 28-29. It was truly an all-school effort! 75 students and staff members were involved. Wonderful set designs and costuming and so many children who learned the script and the songs. Congratulations to everyone who contributed to this production. And a special thanks to Leigh Ann Merrill and Linda Peppe for direction and choreography, stage assistance from Jane Perry, set design from Geoff Merrill, and costume designers June Kelly, Rebecca Roth, and Katty Brennan. And the many others who all had a role in this great show!
